Imo state Governor Emeka Ihedioha, has approved 12 new appointments including that of Adaora Onyechere, a former staff of prominent TV station, AIT as Special Assistant, Information and Advocacy. The appointments which take effect immediately was announced on Wednesday by Chibuike Onyeukwu, Chief Press Secretary to the Governor. Below is the full list of appointments: According to the statement, the Governor believes that their wealth of experience will add value to the rebuilding of the state.